PN,31409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1779440815
OL,3,CCheaper tickets for summer attractions
OL,4,Cand kids meals as Reeves slashes VAT
OL,6,FReeves also confirmed that there would
OL,7,Fbe no rise in fuel duty in 2026, after
OL,8,Fthe government announced the planned
OL,9,Fincrease in fuel duty has been
OL,10,Fscrapped to help motorists faced with
OL,11,Frising pump prices.
OL,13,FConservative shadow chancellor Sir Mel
OL,14,FStride said the "U-turn has finally
OL,15,Fcome" after Rachel Reeves announced a
OL,16,Fdelay to the rise in fuel duty.
OL,26,@vD@QOUwD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1779440815
OL,3,CCheaper tickets for summer attractions
OL,4,Cand kids meals as Reeves slashes VAT
OL,6,FResponding to the Chancellor's
OL,7,Fstatement in the Commons, Stride said:
OL,8,F"It was always obvious that the fuel
OL,9,Fduty increase would need to be
OL,10,Fcancelled. Obvious to everyone except
OL,11,Fthe Chancellor. So can I ask, why did
OL,12,Fthe Chancellor fight us on fuel duty
OL,13,Ffor so long? Why has she been so hell
OL,14,Fbent on raising fuel duty during an
OL,15,Fenergy crisis? Well, inevitably, the U-
OL,16,Fturn has finally come."
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
